NODE_3_length_145402_cov_1582.300836	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	42629	43210	.	+	0	ID=MGA_303;product=haloacid dehalogenase-like hydrolase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011068193.1;translation=MRVFDFDGTIYDGESLFDLYLYSARHDPKVFRYIAPVLRYAVKYKLGRATLEQMEYGVGKMTEGYLTELSRSKRVASVEQLVDDFWDRYYARIKPWYQPESDDVILTASFDLTVGEACRRLGVRNLVASEVDVGTMKVTYLNFSTNKAKRFRELYGPDVVIDEFYTDSKFDQPMIDMARHAFMVKGNTITQVK;locus_tag=LOCUS_03020;note=WP_011068193.1 haloacid dehalogenase-like hydrolase (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:95.9%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:8.3e-104],Domain:cl21460:HAD_like Haloacid Dehalogenase-like Hydrolases. This subfamily includes the uncharacterized Bacillus subtilis YhcW. It belongs to the beta-phosphoglucomutase-like family whose other members include Lactococcus lactis beta-PGM%2C a mutase which catalyzes the interconversion of beta-D-glucose 1-phosphate (G1P) and D-glucose 6-phosphate (G6P)%2C Saccharomyces cerevisiae phosphatases GPP1 and GPP2 that dephosphorylate DL-glycerol-3-phosphate and DOG1 and DOG2 that dephosphorylate 2-deoxyglucose-6-phosphate%2C and Escherichia coli 6-phosphogluconate phosphatase YieH. This family belongs to the haloacid dehalogenase-like (HAD) hydrolases%2C a large superfamily of diverse enzymes that catalyze carbon or phosphoryl group transfer reactions on a range of substrates%2C using an active site aspartate in nucleophilic catalysis. Members of this superfamily include 2-L-haloalkanoic acid dehalogenase%2C azetidine hydrolase%2C phosphonoacetaldehyde hydrolase%2C phosphoserine phosphatase%2C phosphomannomutase%2C P-type ATPases and many others. HAD hydrolases are found in all three kingdoms of life%2C and most genomes are predicted to contain multiple HAD-like proteins. Members possess a highly conserved alpha/beta core domain%2C and many also possess a small cap domain%2C the fold and function of which is variable. HAD hydrolases are sometimes referred to as belonging to the DDDD superfamily of phosphohydrolases. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:3-186%2C Eval:6.6e-07%2C score:45.0],MGA_303
