NODE_5_length_113474_cov_1254.666817	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	31338	32252	.	-	0	ID=MGA_561;product=DNA polymerase III subunit delta;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_007057620.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_05580;gene=holA;EC_number=2.7.7.7;note=WP_007057620.1 DNA polymerase III subunit delta (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:99.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:94.1%25%2C Eval:1.4e-169],Domain:cl27797:DNA_pol3_delt_C Processivity clamp loader gamma complex DNA pol III C-term. DNA polymerase III delta (holA) and delta prime (holB) subunits are distinct proteins encoded by separate genes. The delta prime subunit (holB) exhibits sequence homology to the tau and gamma subunits (dnaX)%2C but the delta subunit (holA) does not demonstrate this same homology with dnaX. The delta%2C delta prime%2C gamma%2C chi and psi subunits form the gamma complex subassembly of DNA polymerase III holoenzyme%2C which couples ATP to assemble the ring-shaped beta subunit around DNA forming a DNA sliding clamp. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-293%2C Eval:9.8e-33%2C score:120.5],MGA_561
