NODE_11_length_81631_cov_2194.542745	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	21179	24919	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1037;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_10300;note=WP_011068664.1 family 43 glycosylhydrolase (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:39.5%25%2C q_cov:52.7%25%2C s_cov:97.6%25%2C Eval:1.6e-124%2C partial hit],Domain:cl14647:GH43_62_32_68 Glycosyl hydrolase families: GH43%2C GH62%2C GH32%2C GH68. The glycosyl hydrolase family 43 contains members that are arabinanases. Arabinanases hydrolyse the alpha-1%2C5-linked L-arabinofuranoside backbone of plant cell wall arabinans. The structure of arabinanase Arb43A from Cellvibrio japonicus reveals a five-bladed beta-propeller fold. A long V-shaped groove%2C partially enclosed at one end%2C forms a single extended substrate-binding surface across the face of the propeller. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:728-1086%2C Eval:1.6e-25%2C score:106.2],MGA_1037
