NODE_16_length_55919_cov_2129.389904	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	52758	53897	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1288;product=cell division ATP-binding protein FtsE;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011068338.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_12780;gene=ftsE;note=WP_011068338.1 cell division ATP-binding protein FtsE (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:89.5%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:8.2e-192],Domain:cl28181:AAA ATPases associated with a variety of cellular activities. Members of this family are ATP-binding cassette (ABC) proteins by homology%2C but belong to energy coupling factor (ECF) transport systems. The architecture in general is two ATPase subunits (or a double-length fusion protein)%2C a T component%2C and a substrate capture (S) component that is highly variable%2C and may be interchangeable in genomes with only one T component. This model identifies many but not examples of the downstream member of the pair of ECF ATPases in Firmicutes and Mollicutes. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Unknown substrate] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:3-225%2C Eval:5.6e-112%2C score:323.4],MGA_1288
