NODE_17_length_55754_cov_1458.347989	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	43854	45029	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1338;product=site-specific integrase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011393297.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_13260;note=WP_011393297.1 site-specific integrase (Moorella thermoacetica) [pid:25.7%25%2C q_cov:90.0%25%2C s_cov:93.6%25%2C Eval:2.0e-18],Domain:cl28330:XerC Integrase [Replication%2C recombination and repair%2C Mobilome: prophages%2C transposons]. The phage integrase family describes a number of recombinases with tyrosine active sites that transiently bind covalently to DNA. Many are associated with mobile DNA elements%2C including phage%2C transposons%2C and phase variation loci. This model represents XerD%2C one of two closely related chromosomal proteins along with XerC (TIGR02224). XerC and XerD are site-specific recombinases which help resolve chromosome dimers to monomers for cell division after DNA replication. In species with a large chromosome and with homologs of XerD on other replicons%2C the chomosomal copy was preferred for building this model. This model does not detect all XerD%2C as some apparent XerD examples score below the trusted and noise cutoff scores. XerC and XerD interact with cell division protein FtsK. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:102-351%2C Eval:4.6e-15%2C score:72.2],MGA_1338
