NODE_22_length_31132_cov_1839.625986	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	15863	16135	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1513;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MEFEYDPAKSAKNLAKHGIDFEAAQRMWDNSKTVTLTAPNPGNDDVRYIVLGMIDGKHWTAITTKRGKRIRIISVRRSRKNEEAYYDSQE;locus_tag=LOCUS_14980;note=WP_080545219.1 BrnT family toxin (Bifidobacterium bifidum) [pid:73.7%25%2C q_cov:63.3%25%2C s_cov:64.8%25%2C Eval:1.7e-18%2C partial hit],frameshifted%2C insertion/deletion at around 16129,Domain:cl01108:BrnT_toxin Ribonuclease toxin%2C BrnT%2C of type II toxin-antitoxin system. BrnT is a ribonuclease toxin of a type II toxin-antitoxin system that exhibits a RelE-like fold. The antitoxin that neutralizes this toxin is pfam14384. BrnT is found in bacteria%2C archaea%2C bacteriophage%2C and plasmids. BrnT-BrnA forms a 2:2 tetrameric complex and autoregulates its own expression%2C which is induced by a number of different environmental stresses. Expression of BrnT alone results in cessation of bacterial growth which can be rescued after subsequent expression of BrnA. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-88%2C Eval:5.0e-20%2C score:74.3],MGA_1513
