NODE_34_length_15262_cov_1863.108594	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	2446	3720	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1747;product=deoxyguanosinetriphosphate triphosphohydrolase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_032740616.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_17250;note=WP_032740616.1 deoxyguanosinetriphosphate triphosphohydrolase (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:98.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:99.1%25%2C Eval:5.2e-246],Domain:cl26231:YdhJ HD superfamily phosphohydrolase [General function prediction only]. dGTP triphosphohydrolase (dgt) releases inorganic triphosphate%2C an unusual activity reaction product%2C from GTP. Its activity has been called limited to the Enterobacteriaceae%2C although homologous sequences are detected elsewhere. This finding casts doubt on whether the activity is shared in other species. In several of these other species%2C the homologous gene is found in an apparent operon with dnaG%2C the DNA primase gene. The enzyme from E. coli was shown to bind coopertatively to single stranded DNA. The biological role of dgt is unknown. [Purines%2C pyrimidines%2C nucleosides%2C and nucleotides%2C Nucleotide and nucleoside interconversions] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:17-424%2C Eval:3.8e-103%2C score:309.6],MGA_1747
