NODE_46_length_8791_cov_1266.725614	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	5490	6563	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1816;product=tyrosine recombinase XerC;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_007058617.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_17880;note=WP_007058617.1 tyrosine recombinase XerC (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:97.8%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:1.3e-194],Domain:cl28330:XerC Integrase [Replication%2C recombination and repair%2C Mobilome: prophages%2C transposons]. The phage integrase family describes a number of recombinases with tyrosine active sites that transiently bind covalently to DNA. Many are associated with mobile DNA elements%2C including phage%2C transposons%2C and phase variation loci. This model represents XerD%2C one of two closely related chromosomal proteins along with XerC (TIGR02224). XerC and XerD are site-specific recombinases which help resolve chromosome dimers to monomers for cell division after DNA replication. In species with a large chromosome and with homologs of XerD on other replicons%2C the chomosomal copy was preferred for building this model. This model does not detect all XerD%2C as some apparent XerD examples score below the trusted and noise cutoff scores. XerC and XerD interact with cell division protein FtsK. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-357%2C Eval:6.5e-97%2C score:287.2],MGA_1816
